    <section class="tips">
        <h2 class="egt">Essential Gardening Tips</h2>
<div class="tip-list" >
        <article>
            <h3>Tip #1: Start with Quality Soil</h3>
            <p>Healthy plants begin with healthy soil. Invest in rich, well-draining soil to give your plants the best start.</p>
        </article>

        <article>
            <h3>Tip #2: Water in the Morning</h3>
            <p>Watering early in the day reduces evaporation and helps prevent fungal growth. Aim to water at the base of plants for best results.</p>
        </article>

        <article>
            <h3>Tip #3: Choose Plants Wisely</h3>
            <p>Pick plants suited to your climate and garden conditions. Native plants generally require less maintenance and are more resilient.</p>
        </article>

        <article>
            <h3>Tip #4: Compost Regularly</h3>
            <p>Composting adds valuable nutrients to the soil and promotes sustainable gardening. Start a compost pile with kitchen scraps and yard waste.</p>
        </article>

        <article>
            <h3>Tip #5: Prune for Healthy Growth</h3>
            <p>Pruning encourages healthy growth and removes dead or diseased parts of plants. Use sharp, clean tools and prune during the dormant season.</p>
        </article>

        <article>
            <h3>Tip #6: Rotate Your Crops</h3>
            <p>Crop rotation prevents soil depletion and helps manage pests. Plan to plant different crops in various spots in your garden each season.</p>
        </article>
    </div>
    </section>
